When you have an application and if it grows,

5
00:00:11,130 --> 00:00:14,940
you have many more data, what if you have 10 view data

6
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:17,940
and 5 view bags that you are using?

7
00:00:17,940 --> 00:00:19,680
Things will start getting ugly

8
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,990
because when you will look at the view,

9
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:23,070
you will not be able

10
00:00:23,070 --> 00:00:26,583
to easily identify where this is coming from.

11
00:00:27,630 --> 00:00:31,590
And the reason I am saying is our view is tightly bounded

12
00:00:31,590 --> 00:00:33,270
to this product model,

13
00:00:33,270 --> 00:00:36,813
but product model does not have all the data that is needed.

14
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:40,590
So typically I avoid using viewbags

15
00:00:40,590 --> 00:00:44,100
and view data as much as possible.

16
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:47,940
The alternative to that is to tightly bind your view

17
00:00:47,940 --> 00:00:50,160
to the object that you want.

18
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,290
If object is not a simple object,

19
00:00:52,290 --> 00:00:55,020
you can create a combination of object

20
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:57,513
and that is called as view model.

21
00:00:58,350 --> 00:01:00,660
View model as the name suggests,

22
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:03,693
it is a model which is specific for a view.

23
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:07,230
So let me show you how to do that

24
00:01:07,230 --> 00:01:10,740
